<Docs title="pnpm Workspaces" description="How Dep Beacon resolves pnpm workspace catalogs.">
  <h1>pnpm Workspaces</h1>
  <p>
    Dep Beacon scans workspace `pnpm-workspace.yaml` files and builds a catalog snapshot before analyzing package manifests.
  </p>

  <h2>Default catalog</h2>
  <pre><code>catalog:
  astro: ^7.0.0
  typescript: ^6.0.3</code></pre>

  <p>
    A `package.json` dependency like `"astro": "catalog:"` is analyzed using the catalog range.
  </p>

  <h2>Named catalogs</h2>
  <pre><code>catalogs:
  react19:
    react: ^19.0.0
    react-dom: ^19.0.0</code></pre>

  <p>
    A dependency using `"react": "catalog:react19"` resolves against the named catalog.
  </p>

  <h2>Workspace dependency maps</h2>
  <p>
    Dep Beacon also analyzes workspace `overrides` and `packageExtensions` so central dependency policy gets the same status signals as package manifests.
  </p>
</Docs>
